        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11806",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not evaluated yet for quality yet, but:\n\nhttp:\/\/pear.php.net\/package\/PHP_Beautifier\n\nMost recent release was in June, built in PHP 5.  Works on the command line, and you write custom rules.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-12-06T10:37:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-12-06T10:37:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11807",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That should read, \"you can write custom rules if you like.\"\n\nHere's a command line usage guide: \nhttp:\/\/php.apsique.com\/PHP_Beautifier\/PHP_Beautifier\/tutorial_PHP_Beautifier.howtouse.commandline.pkg.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-12-06T10:42:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-12-06T10:42:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11810",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "These tools require a non-trivial effort to configure and setup \"profiles\".\nIf someone takes the initiative of codifying the ZF coding standards into configurations for these tools, then the chance for adoption would increase.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-12-06T12:15:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-12-06T12:15:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11811",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've had bad luck with automated code beautifiers.  The risk is that there's some obscure corner case that the code beautifier doesn't handle well, and it inadvertently _changes_ the functionality of the code and introduces bugs.  \n\nThis actually happened on a Java project I was on in 2005.  We upgraded from Java 1.4 to Java 5 and the code beautifier tools didn't know about the new syntax in that release, so they totally ruined the code in the process of trying to beautify it.\n\nIt would be one thing to have a tool check and report mismatches between the code and the coding standard, but I wouldn't want it committing changes without a human reviewing them first.  Code beautifiers should be run manually and then the results checked visually and with unit tests.\n\nWe also have some points in our draft coding standards document that are not simply syntactic issues.  So enforcement by a code beautifier is not a complete solution.  Still, some automation is better than none.  \n\nMatthew, if you want to write a profile that does best-effort checks with respect to the Zend Framework coding standard, that would be much appreciated. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-12-06T13:19:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-12-06T13:19:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11812",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The pre-commit SVN hook we previously discussed for code analysis\/beautifier tools might simply result in an email under certain conditions instead of doing something drastic.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
